I just know you're talking about {{item:3165}} here {{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}} 

That item is currently the crutch that allows mages to have a mid game still.  If you were to reduce the AP on that, mages would lose wave control, poke, and burst, the 3 things that they are supposed to be best at.

I am in full support of a (carefully planned and tested) update to mage itemization in general.  Still, the other AP/CDR items already have significantly lowered AP (-30 on the actual mage ones compared to the raw AP alternatives).  If they lose much more, they'll either need a price drop (making them more oppressive early due to unique effects but much weaker in the late game) or they'll just cease being purchased altogether.

I'm pretty sure season 4 still had cdr items scarce, it was at the start of the adc update was when cdr became more frequent in items

