> Pretty sure some jungle items also had cdr

Technically Trinity Force didn't have it until late 2015, so you have a mild point (long enough to feel like forever)

Some of these changes were so that Riot could bring down the damage of the item the CDR was added to, btw. Almost every CDR change was the result of a removal of AD, or AP from an item. Sheen lost 20 AP. Armor pen items lost 15 AD. Zhonya's lost 30 AP. Abyssal lost all its AP. Banshee's lost some AP.

So basically what Riot has done: remove damage, add cdr, but give the option to get that damage back if you get a specific rune.

Keep in mind.... the items you just listed are still the core CDR items everyone uses, and used then. Tbh, I can't remember a time when AD's or junglers didn't build Spirit Visage or Frozen heart along with Black cleaver or Youmuu's.

So capping or close to capping CDR isn't anything new. What's new is.... the ability to do it on an all out AD item build (AP already did CDR and had the AP)
